      "message": "this isn\u0027t a good way of returning a value from waitWithTimeout()\n\nthe caller usually only cares about single thing: is the process still alive after function returns or not. So the return value is supposed to be at least |true| if there was no process with |pid| or it exited before the timeout, and |false| in case of timing out while process is still running. You could also create an enum { Exited, Timeout, Error } if you want to give more information back; or use an int as a poor man\u0027s enum with \u003c0, 0, 1 as values - like in Posix\n\nBut mixing together \u0027there was no such process\u0027 and \u0027failed to allocated memory\u0027 will make the function very tricky to use correctly.",
